<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4688473>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 3. — A-H, Strictocostella? spinosa (d’Orbigny, 1846); A, topotype (Baden) (MNHN F62163); B, topotype (Baden) (MNHN F62164); C, lectotype (MNHN FO 45); D, E, enlargements of A; F, enlargement of A showing the chamber basal spines; G, H, enlargements of B showing (arrows) the alternating costae running from a part of a chamber to another part of the next chamber; I, J, Nonion commune (d’Orbigny,1846),specimen from Baden (MNHN F62166); K-M, Nonion boueanum (d’Orbigny, 1846); K, specimen from Baden (MNHN F62165); M, lectotype (MNHN FO 94). Scale bars: 100 μm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4688473/files/figure.png" .

